            function climatol(){
                //   ifr(10);
                var oceano= document.getElementById('clim_ond').oceano.value;
                if (oceano == 'ani') {
                    document.clim_ond.dia.disabled = true;
                    var mes= document.getElementById('clim_ond').mes.value;
                    var imageN="http://img0.cptec.inpe.br/~rgrafico/portal_ondas/climatologia/alt_ondas/"+oceano+"_pn_"+mes+".gif";

                    var imageN="http://img0.cptec.inpe.br/~rgrafico/portal_ondas/climatologia/alt_ondas/"+oceano+"_ado_"+dia+"_"+mes+".png";
                }
   
                $.colorbox({iframe:true, innerWidth:600, innerHeight:615, href:imageN}); 

            }

            function figura(){
                // ifr(10);

                var dia= document.getElementById('formfig').dia.value;

function tabua_mares(){
                var cidade= document.getElementById('tab_mares').cidade.value;
                var ano= document.getElementById('tab_mares').ano.value;
                var mes= document.getElementById('tab_mares').mes.value;
                var imageName="/~rondas/mares/index.php?cod="+cidade+"&mes="+mes+"&ano="+ano;
		
                $.colorbox({iframe:true, innerWidth:830, innerHeight:730, href:imageName}); 
            }

            function go5(imageName,imageWidth,imageHeight) {
                newWindow = window.open(imageName,"newWindow",",resizable=yes,scrollbars=no,width="+imageWidth+",height="+imageHeight);
            }

              function ifr(val)
            {
                tags= Array("p2");

                if(val == 10){
                    document.getElementById('pframe').style.visibility="visible";
                    document.getElementById('pframe').style.display="block";
                    document.getElementById('pvol').style.visibility="visible";
                    document.getElementById('pvol').style.display="block";        
                    for (d=0;d<tags.length;d++){
                        var tg = tags[d];
                        document.getElementById(tg).style.visibility="hidden";
                        document.getElementById(tg).style.display="none";
                    }       
                }

                else{
                    document.getElementById('pframe').style.visibility="hidden";
                    document.getElementById('pframe').style.display="none";          
                    document.getElementById('pvol').style.visibility="hidden";
                    document.getElementById('pvol').style.display="none";   
                    for (d=0;d<tags.length;d++){
                        var tg = tags[d];
                        document.getElementById(tg).style.visibility="visible";
                        document.getElementById(tg).style.display="block";
                    }
                }
            }


            function chamar()
            {
                // 
                               window.onLoad=changecontent();
            }
        </script>

                        <!--inico aviso --><div class="sub">O modelo de Ondas OceÂnicas </div>
                        <div class="ult">
                            <div id="av1">A implementação global do modelo de ondas oceânicas de terceira geração WAVEWATCH 2.22 produz uma previsão diária no horário 0h GMT (diminua 3h para obter o horário de Brasília, 2h no horário de verão). Como forçantes, este modelo utiliza campos de ventos produzidos pelo modelo atmosférico global AVN do NCEP.<br />
                                Para saber mais sobre a implementação do modelo WWATCH no CPTEC. <a href="/exp_wwatch.shtml" class="iframe"><img src="/~rondas/common/img/mais.gif" border="0"></a><br />Maiores informações sobre o Modelo de Ondas Oceânicas WAVEWATCH.
                                <a href="http://polar.ncep.noaa.gov/waves/wavewatch/wavewatch.html" target="_blank"><img src="/~rondas/common/img/mais.gif" border="0"></a><br />

                                closetag=''
                                var fwidth=222 //set scroller width
                                var fheight=95 //set scroller height

                                var fadescheme=0 //set 0 to fade text color from (white to black), 1 for (black to white)
                                var fadelinks=1  //should links inside scroller content also fade like text? 0 for no, 1 for yes.

                                ///No need to edit below this line/////////////////

                                var hex=(fadescheme==0)? 255 : 0
                                var startcolor=(fadescheme==0)? "rgb(125,125,125)" : "rgb(125,125,125)"
                                var endcolor=(fadescheme==0)? "rgb(125,125,125)" : "rgb(125,125,125)"

                                var ie4=document.all&&!document.getElementById
                                var ns4=document.layers
                                var DOM2=document.getElementById
                                var faderdelay=0
                                var index=0

                                if (DOM2)
                                    faderdelay=2000

                                //function to change content
                                function changecontent(){
                                    if (index>=fcontent.length)
                                        index=0
                                    if (DOM2){
                                        document.getElementById("fscroller").style.color=startcolor
                                        document.getElementById("fscroller").innerHTML=begintag+fcontent[index]+closetag
                                        linksobj=document.getElementById("fscroller").getElementsByTagName("A")
                                        if (fadelinks)
                                            linkcolorchange(linksobj)
                                        colorfade()
                                    }
                                    else if (ie4)
                                        document.all.fscroller.innerHTML=begintag+fcontent[index]+closetag
                                    else if (ns4){
                                        document.fscrollerns.document.fscrollerns_sub.document.write(begintag+fcontent[index]+closetag)
                                        document.fscrollerns.document.fscrollerns_sub.document.close()
                                    }

                                    index++
                                    setTimeout("changecontent()",delay+faderdelay)
                                }

                                // colorfade() partially by Marcio Galli for Netscape Communications.  ////////////
                                // Modified by Dynamicdrive.com

                                frame=20;

                                function linkcolorchange(obj){
                                    if (obj.length>0){
                                        for (i=0;i<obj.length;i++)
                                            obj[i].style.color="rgb("+hex+","+hex+","+hex+")"
                                    }
                                }

                                function colorfade() {	         	
                                    // 20 frames fading process
                                    if(frame>0) {	
                                        hex=(fadescheme==0)? hex-12 : hex+12 // increase or decrease color value depd on fadescheme
                                        document.getElementById("fscroller").style.color="rgb("+hex+","+hex+","+hex+")"; // Set color value.
                                        if (fadelinks)
                                            linkcolorchange(linksobj)
                                        frame--;
                                        setTimeout("colorfade()",20);	
                                    }

                                    else{
                                        document.getElementById("fscroller").style.color=endcolor;
                                        frame=20;
                                        hex=(fadescheme==0)? 255 : 0
                                    }   
                                }
                                if (ie4||DOM2)
                                    document.write('<div id="fscroller" style="border:0px solid black;width:'+fwidth+';height:'+fheight+';padding:0px"></div>')
                            </script>
                            <ilayer id="fscrollerns" width=&{fwidth}; height=&{fheight};> 
                                <layer id="fscrollerns_sub" width=&{fwidth}; height=&{fheight}; left=0 top=0></layer>
                            </ilayer>
                        </div>
                        <div class="leg">Atualizado: 27/03/2017 </div>
                    </div>

		<script type="text/javascript">
			//---------------------------------------------------------

			function onPopupDialog(strDialogURL, strWidth, strHeight, strCustomData)
			{
				var strOpenURL = strDialogURL+"&CustomData="+strCustomData;

				if(strOpenURL.search("ServiceInstUID")==-1)
					strOpenURL += "&ServiceInstUID={D2ADD0F5-7870-444F-9544-C1A0D6A52E57}";

				
				strOpenURL += "&ItemID={523C0CCD-3E65-47DD-A811-23D3C0B3D9CF}";
				

				var intTop = (screen.height-strHeight)/2;
				var intLeft = (screen.width-strWidth)/2;
				if (intTop > 16)
					intTop -=16;
				window.open(strOpenURL, "_blank", "TOP="+intTop+",SCREENY="+intTop+",HEIGHT="+strHeight+",LEFT="+intLeft+",SCREENX="+intLeft+",WIDTH="+strWidth+",resizable,scrollbars");
			}


			//---------------------------------------------------------

			function onWorkFlowActionChanged()
			{
				if(document.getElementById("_EZTAssignedToUser_"))
					document.getElementById("_EZTAssignedToUser_").value="";

				if(document.getElementById("_EZTAssignedToUser_Display"))
					document.getElementById("_EZTAssignedToUser_Display").innerText = "";

				return true;
			}

			//---------------------------------------------------------

			function LumisOnTextCountChanged(pObjSource, strDestID)
			{
				var iSize = pObjSource.value.length;

				if(document.getElementById(strDestID))
					document.getElementById(strDestID).innerText=iSize;

				return true;
			}

  var OT_DELAY = 180000;
  REFRESH_TIMEOUT = null;

  function iniciarRefresh() {
      REFRESH_TIMEOUT = setTimeout(function () {
          window.location.reload();
      }, OT_DELAY);

<script>

	var menuOffset = 300;
	$(document).on("scroll", function(){
	       var docScroll = $(document).scrollTop();
	       if(docScroll >= menuOffset) { 
	           $("#floating-bar").addClass("fixed");
			   $("#floating-bar").slideDown(300);
	           //dynamically change the width of floating bar according to it's width of previous state 
	       }else {
			   $("#floating-bar").slideUp(300,function(){
				   $("#floating-bar").removeClass("fixed");
			   });
	       }
	});


</script>

<script>
	var validator;
	jQuery().ready(function() {
	 	var validation = {
		 	rules: {
		 		reset_loginname: {
	            	required: true,
	                email: true
	            }
		 	},
            messages:{
            	reset_loginname:{
                	required:"O campo email é obrigatório",
                    email:"O campo email precisa ser preenchido com um email válido"
            	}
            },
            submitHandler: function(form) {
            	$(form).find("#bt-login").attr("disabled",true);	
				sempre.login.resetPassword(form);
			}
		 }

	 	validator = jQuery("#floatForgottenPasswordForm").validate(validation);
	});
	
</script>

<script>
	var validator;
	jQuery().ready(function() {
	 	var validation = {
		 	rules: {
		 		login_loginname: {
	            	required: true,
	                email: true
	            },
	            login_password:{
	            	required:true
	            }
		 	},
            messages:{
            	login_loginname:{
                	required:"O campo email é obrigatório",
                    email:"O campo email precisa ser preenchido com um email válido"
            	},
            	 login_password:{
 	            	required:"O campo senha é obrigatório"
 	            }
            },
            submitHandler: function(form) {
            	$(form).find("#bt-login").attr("disabled",true);	
				sempre.login.login(form);
			}
		 }

	 	validator = jQuery("#floatLoginForm").validate(validation);
	});
	
</script>

<div class="twelve columns busca-assunto" data-elemento="cinema-filtror">
    <div class="twelve columns info">
        <div class="twelve columns">
            <div class="row input">
                <div class="six columns align-left"">
                    <select id="PorFilme">
                        <option value="">-- Filmes --</option>
                    </select>
                </div>

                </div>

                        <option value="">-- Cinemas --</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div class="six columns align-right">
                    <input id="PalavraChave" placeholder="Palavra-chave" type="text" value="">
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="twelve columns buscar-filme">
                <button id="BuscaFilme" class="btn">Buscar</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script type="text/javascript">
    function abreFiltro() {
        var id = $(this).attr("id");
        var value = $(this).val();

        window.location.href = "/diversão/roteiros-culturais/cinema?" + id + "=" + value;
    }

    $("#BuscaFilme").click(function () {
        var valor = $("#PalavraChave").val();
        if (valor) {
            window.location.href = "/diversão/roteiros-culturais/cinema?busca=" + valor;
        }

        return false;
    });


    var $SELECTS = [$("#PorFilme"), $("#PorGenero"), $("#PorCinema")];

    var json = {"CinemaFiltros":{"PorFilme":{"Registro":[{"ID":"2864","Valor":"A Bela e a Fera"},{"ID":"2876","Valor":"A Grande Muralha"},{"ID":"2860","Valor":"Cinquenta Tons Mais Escuros"},{"ID":"2903","Valor":"Era o Hotel Cambridge"},{"ID":"2900","Valor":"Fragmentado"},{"ID":"2895","Valor":"Hiroshima, Meu Amor"},{"ID":"2890","Valor":"Insubstitu\u00edvel"},{"ID":"2875","Valor":"Internet - O Filme"},{"ID":"2888","Valor":"Kong: A Ilha da Caveira"},{"ID":"2865","Valor":"Lego Batman - O Filme"},{"ID":"2873","Valor":"Lion - Uma Jornada para Casa"},{"ID":"2878","Valor":"Logan"},{"ID":"2881","Valor":"Moonlight: Sob a Luz do Luar"},{"ID":"2897","Valor":"O Filho de Joseph"},{"ID":"2896","Valor":"Pedro Osmar, Pra Liberdade Que Se Conquista"},{"ID":"2902","Valor":"Power Rangers"},{"ID":"2901","Valor":"T2 Trainspotting"},{"ID":"2827","Valor":"Tinha que Ser Ele? (*)"}]},"PorGenero":{"Registro":[{"ID":"1","Valor":"A\u00e7\u00e3o"},{"ID":"2","Valor":"Anima\u00e7\u00e3o"},{"ID":"3","Valor":"Aventura"},{"ID":"4","Valor":"Com\u00e9dia"},{"ID":"19","Valor":"Com\u00e9dia Dram\u00e1tica"},{"ID":"6","Valor":"Document\u00e1rio"},{"ID":"7","Valor":"Drama"},{"ID":"16","Valor":"Drama \/ Romance"},{"ID":"20","Valor":"Fantasia"},{"ID":"13","Valor":"Suspense"}]},"PorCinema":{"Registro":[{"ID":"14","Valor":"Belas"},{"ID":"19","Valor":"Betim "},{"ID":"2","Valor":"BH Shopping (Cineplex)"},{"ID":"3","Valor":"Big"},{"ID":"681","Valor":"Boulevard"},{"ID":"299","Valor":"Cidade"},{"ID":"686","Valor":"Contagem"},{"ID":"10","Valor":"Del Rey"},{"ID":"11","Valor":"Diamond Mall (Cineplex)"},{"ID":"683","Valor":"Esta\u00e7\u00e3o BH"},{"ID":"13","Valor":"Ita\u00fa Power Shopping"},{"ID":"12","Valor":"Minas Shopping"},{"ID":"688","Valor":"Monte Carmo "},{"ID":"16","Valor":"Norte"},{"ID":"15","Valor":"Pampulha Mall"},{"ID":"18","Valor":"Paragem"},{"ID":"687","Valor":"Partage Shopping Betim"},{"ID":"8","Valor":"P\u00e1tio Savassi (Cinemark)"},{"ID":"21","Valor":"Ponteio"},{"ID":"20","Valor":"Via Shopping"}]}}};
    var cf = json.CinemaFiltros;

    for (var i in $SELECTS) {
        var $select = $SELECTS[i];
        $select.on("change", abreFiltro);
        var id = $select.attr("id");

        var dados = cf[id].Registro;

        for (var j in dados) {
            var item = dados[j];

            var $option = $("<option value='" + item.ID + "'>" + item.Valor + "</option>")

            $select.append($option);
        }
    }

    $("#PorFilme").val("");
    $("#PorGenero").val("");
    $("#PorCinema").val("");


</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
	jQuery(document).ready(function($){
		// Hide all the tooltips
		$("#ndq-tools a").each(function() {
			$("strong", this).css("opacity", "0");
		});
		
		$("#ndq-tools a").hover(function() { // Mouse over
			//$(this)
				//.stop().fadeTo(300, 1)
				//.siblings().stop().fadeTo(300, 0.3)
	
			$("strong", this)
				.stop()
				.animate({
					opacity: 1,
					top: "0px"				
				}, 300);
			
		}, function() { // Mouse out
			//$(this)
				//.stop().fadeTo(300, 1)
				//.siblings().stop().fadeTo(300, 1)
				
			$("strong", this)
				.stop()
				.animate({
					opacity: 0,
					top: "0px"
				}, 300);
		});
	});
</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
	var allFilter = true;
    /*top section fullscreen*/
    var header;
    var mainheigth;
    var sectionbackground;
    $(function() {
        $('input[name=tos_agree]').on('click',function(event)
        {
        	if ($(this).prop('checked'))
            {
            	$("#agree_tooltipTop").hide();
            	$("#agree_tooltipBot").hide();
            }
            
        });
        $('form.signupForm a.signupButton').on('click',function(event)
        {
            event.preventDefault();
            $("#agree_tooltipTop").hide();
            $("#agree_tooltipBot").hide();
            var theForm = $(this).parents('form.signupForm');
            if (theForm.attr('name') == 'signupFormTop')
            {
            	if (!$('#agree').prop('checked'))
                {
            		$("#agree_tooltipTop").show();
                    return;
                }
            }
            if (theForm.attr('name') == 'signupFormBottom')
            {
            	if (!$('#agreeBot').prop('checked'))
                {
            		$("#agree_tooltipBot").show();
                    return;
                } 
            }
            theForm.submit();
        });
        
        header = $('#header').outerHeight(true);
        mainheigth = $(window).height();
        sectionbackground = $('#mainlaunch').height( mainheigth - header );

        if ( typeof( PasswordStrengthChecker ) != 'undefined' )
        {
        	var passInputTop = $('form[name=signupFormTop] input[name=password]');
        	var passInputBottom = $('form[name=signupFormBottom] input[name=password]');
        	var passcheck = new PasswordStrengthChecker( passInputTop, passInputTop, 6, 'top');	
        	var passcheck2 = new PasswordStrengthChecker( passInputBottom, passInputBottom, 6, 'bottom' );
        }

        $('form.signupForm input[type=password]').on('keyup', function () {$('#agree_tooltipTop').hide();$('#agree_tooltipBot').hide()});
        $('form.signupForm input[type=password]').on('focus', function () {$('#agree_tooltipTop').hide();$('#agree_tooltipBot').hide()});
        
        $("#filtering a").on('click',function(event)
        {
            event.preventDefault();
            var theButton = $(this);
            var filter = theButton.attr('filter');
            if (filter == 'none')
            {
            	$("#filtering a").removeClass('active');
            	$("div.single-template").fadeIn();
            	theButton.addClass('active');
            	allFilter = true;
            }
            else
            {
                if (allFilter)
                {
                	$("div.single-template").fadeOut();
                	allFilter = false;
                }
                
                $('a.filter[filter=none]').removeClass('active');
				if (theButton.hasClass('active'))
				{
					theButton.removeClass('active');
					if ($("#filtering a.active").length == 0)
					{
						$("#filtering a[filter=none]").addClass('active');
						allFilter = true;
						$("div.single-template").fadeIn();
					}
					else
						$("div.single-template."+filter).fadeOut();
				}
				else
				{
					theButton.addClass('active');
					$("div.single-template."+filter).fadeIn();
				}
            }        
        });
    });

    $(window).on('resize', function(){
        header = $('#header').outerHeight(true);
        mainheigth = $(window).height();
        mainwidth = $(window).outerWidth();
        
        if (mainwidth > 748) {
        	 sectionbackground = $('#mainlaunch').height( mainheigth - header );
        } else {
        	$('#mainlaunch').css({ 
        		  width: 'auto',
        		  height: 'auto'
        		});
        }
        
        
       
    });
    $(".select, .radio, .checkbox").uniform();

    $('#pushdown').on('click', function(e) {
        var aHrefName = $(this).attr('href').substring(1);
        var headingPos = $('#outer-wrapper').find('#' + aHrefName).offset().top;
        $('html, body').not(':animated').animate({scrollTop: headingPos }, 1000);
        e.preventDefault();
    });
</script>

jQuery(document).ready(function() {
jQuery("#elements_itemcategoryvalue").on("change", function()
{
    
    var count = 0;
    
    for (var i = 0; i < this.options.length; i++)
    {
        var option = this.options[i];
        
        option.selected ? count++ : null;
        
        if (count > 3)
        {
            option.selected = false;
            option.disabled = true;
        }else{
            option.disabled = false;
        }
    }
});
});

<div class="row-fluid">
    <div class="span6">
        <h2>How Can I Help?</h2>
        <p>Everyone has a skill, and the Joomla! project would love to discover it! Whether its answering a simple question in the forum, helping to design a flyer for a Joomla! conference, translating text from one language to another, teaching CSS, HTML, javascript or PHP, and everything in between; there is a place for everyone.</p>
        <p>Browse the Joomla! teams to find a group of your interest and get involved!</p>
        <p>
            <a href="/register" class="btn"><span class="icon-chevron-right"></span>Create a Joomler account!            </a>
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="span6">
        <h2>Why Should I Help?</h2>
        <p>The Joomla! project is an all volunteer organisation. That is what sets us apart from other large Open Source projects. By volunteering, you join a large, international and diverse group of passionate individuals, looking to empower people and companies to connect, communicate, and be competitive on the world wide web.</p>
        <p>See what other Joomla! Volunteers - Joomlers - are contributing to the Joomla! project.</p>
        <p>
            <a href="/joomlers" class="btn"><span class="icon-chevron-right"></span>Get to know Joomlers!            </a>
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<br>

                    <h3 class="report-title">
                        <a href="/teams/certification-operations-team/reports/476-call-for-volunteers-certification-operations-team">

                    </h3>
                    <p class="muted">
						By                        <a href="/joomlers/312-luca-marzo">Luca Marzo</a>

                    </p>
                    <p>The Certification Operations Team is responsible to create, maintain and follow the workflow and the processes for the Operations of the Joomla! Certification Program.
In order to improve the efficiency and the effectiveness of the process management, COT needs a new Joomla! extension to handle the Partners application process.
The workflow extension will receive the...</p>

        <div class="well joomlastory">
            <h2>A Joomler Story</h2>
            <ul class="media-list">
                <li class="media">
                    <a class="pull-left" href="/joomlers/61-matthew-baylor">
						<img class="img-rounded" alt="Matthew Baylor" src="/images/volunteers/thumbs/matthew-baylor_50x50.png"/>                    </a>
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h3 class="media-heading">
                            <a href="/joomlers/61-matthew-baylor">
								Matthew Baylor                            </a>
                        </h3>
                        <p class="muted">
                            <span class="icon-location"></span> Marysville, United States                        </p>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li class="media">
                    <p>In 2007 I ran a small side business with a flash/html website. Being frustrated trying to figure out how to change things I found Mambo/Joomla when searching for an alternative platform that was easier to manage. Fast forward a few years I went to design school and started my own webdesign business primarily focused on creating Joomla websites. After awhile I felt that using a free software platform it was only right to give back in some way so I volunteered to help with the Joomla Extensions...</p>
                    <a href="/joomlers/61-matthew-baylor#joomlastory" class="btn">
                        <span class="icon-chevron-right"></span>Read full Joomla Story                    </a>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

China","image":"https:\/\/volunteers.joomla.org\/images\/volunteers\/thumbs\/c741_photo_50x50.jpg"},{"title":"Yves Hoppe","lat":"48.1351253","lng":"11.5819806","url":"\/joomlers\/683-yves-hoppe","address":"Munich, Germany","image":"https:\/\/volunteers.joomla.org\/images\/volunteers\/thumbs\/7021_yves-hoppe_50x50.jpg"},{"title":"Zurab Cherkezishvili","lat":"32.1656221","lng":"-82.9000751","url":"\/joomlers\/1556-zurab-cherkezishvili","address":"Georgia","image":"https:\/\/volunteers.joomla.org\/images\/joomla_50x50.png"} ];

        var icon = {
            url: "media/com_volunteers/images/joomla.png", // url
            scaledSize: new google.maps.Size(50, 50), // scaled size
            origin: new google.maps.Point(0, 0), // origin
            anchor: new google.maps.Point(25, 25) // anchor
        };

        for (i = 0; i < locations.length; i++) {
            marker = new google.maps.Marker({
                position: new google.maps.LatLng(locations[i].lat, locations[i].lng),
                map: map,
                icon: icon
            });

            google.maps.event.addListener(marker, 'click', (function (marker, i, infoWindow) {
                return function () {
                    infoWindow.setContent('<div style="width:200px;"><img width="40" class="pull-left" style="padding-right: 10px" src="' + locations[i].image + '" /><a href="' + locations[i].url + '">' + locations[i].title + '</a><br />' + locations[i].address + '</div>');
                    infoWindow.open(map, marker);
                }
            })(marker, i, infoWindow));

            markers.push(marker);
            bounds.extend(marker.position);
            oms.addMarker(marker);
        }

        var markerCluster = new MarkerClusterer(map, markers, mcOptions);

        var styles = [
            {
                featureType: "road",
                elementType: "geometry",
                stylers: [
                    {lightness: 100},
                    {visibility: "simplified"}
                ]
            }, {
                featureType: "road",
                elementType: "labels",
                stylers: [
                    {visibility: "simplified"}
                ]
            }, {
                featureType: "poi",
                elementType: "labels",
                stylers: [
                    {visibility: "on"}
                ]
            }, {
                featureType: "poi.business",
                elementType: "labels",
                stylers: [
                    {visibility: "off"}
                ]
            }, {
                featureType: "water",
                elementType: "labels",
                stylers: [
                    {visibility: "on"}
                ]
            }
        ];
        map.fitBounds(bounds);
        map.setOptions({styles: styles});
    }

    google.maps.event.addDomListener(window, 'load', initialise);
</script>

        <section class="span2 offset2">

        </section>
        <section class="span5 offset1">
            <h1>
                <em>phpDocumentor</em> analyzes your <em>code</em><br />
                to create great <em>documentation</em>
            </h1>
            <p>
                phpDocumentor enables you to generate documentation from your PHP
                source code. This documentation provides an in-depth view of your
                project to you, your consumers and contributors.
            </p>
            <a class="button demo" href="http://demo.phpdoc.org">Demo</a>
            <a class="button learn-more" href="http://phpdoc.org/docs/latest">Learn more</a>
        </section>
    </header>
</section>

<section class="container">

    <section class="row">
        <section class="span8">
            <article class="content-overview tab-content">
                <h1>
                    <nav>
                        <a href="#why-use-phpdocumentor" class="active">Why use phpDocumentor</a>
                                                                    </nav>
                </h1>

                <section id="why-use-phpdocumentor" class="tab-pane active">
                    <section>
                        <h2>What is phpDocumentor?</h2>
                        <img
                            src="/bundles/phpdocumentorwebsite/images/icons/icon_logo_green.png"
                            alt="phpDocumentor"
                        />

                        <p>
                            phpDocumentor 2 is a tool that makes it possible to generate documentation directly from your PHP
                            source code. With this you can provide your consumers with more information regarding the
                            functionality embedded within your source and not just what is usable to them from your user
                            interface.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            Documentation generated by phpDocumentor 2 does not aim to be a replacement for conventional
                            documentation but is rather supplemental, or reference, documentation.This proves to be
                            useful in the following example situations:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Sets of libraries or applications providing an API, such as phpDocumentor 2 itself</li>
                            <li>Frameworks, such as Zend Framework or Symfony</li>
                            <li>Pluggable architectures, such as WordPress or PyroCMS</li>
                            <li>Long-running, complex projects, to help you find the right function or method for the job</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <h2>Templates</h2>
                        <img
                                src="/bundles/phpdocumentorwebsite/images/icons/icon_templates_green.png"
                                alt="Templates"
                                />

                        <p>
                            phpDocumentor 2 contains an incredibly flexible template system which enables you to alter
                            your output in any way imaginable. This can range from simply applying your own branding
                            for the HTML output by merely altering a couple of CSS files to determining which types of
                            output are generated and where they are made available.
                        </p>
                    </section>
                    <section>
                        <h2>Code Analysis</h2>
                        <img
                                src="/bundles/phpdocumentorwebsite/images/icons/icon_charts_green.png"
                                alt="Code Analysis"
                                />

                        <p>
                            phpDocumentor 2 is capable of extracting interesting information and presenting it in the
                            form of graphs and reports. The following are currently supported:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>An inheritance diagram showing all subclassing and implementing of interfaces.</li>
                            <li>Reporting errors in your source code's inline documentation.</li>
                            <li>Reporting which elements are marked as deprecated.</li>
                            <li>Reporting where TODOs are placed in your code and what is to be done.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>
                            This list will only grow in the future to help you determine where to invest your resources
                            in order to make your code more stable and maintainable.
                        </p>
                    </section>
                </section>

                <section id="getting-started" class="tab-pane">
                    <section>
                        <h2>How does it work?</h2>
                    </section>

        </section>

        <section class="span4" id="quickstart">
            <article id="installing">
                <h2>Installing</h2>
                <div class="accordion" id="installation">
                    <div class="accordion-group">
                        <div class="accordion-heading">
                            <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#installation" href="#install-pear">
                                <i class="icon-chevron-right"></i> Using PEAR
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <div id="install-pear" class="accordion-body collapse in">
                            <div class="accordion-inner">
                                <p>With <a href="">PEAR</a> installed, please run the following commands:</p>
                                <pre><code class="language-php">pear channel-discover pear.phpdoc.org
pear install phpdoc/phpDocumentor</code></pre>
                                <p>
                                    Once the installation is complete a global command, called <code>phpdoc</code>, will be
                                    available.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-group">
                        <div class="accordion-heading">
                            <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#installation" href="#install-composer">
                                <i class="icon-chevron-right"></i> Using Composer
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <div id="install-composer" class="accordion-body collapse">
                            <div class="accordion-inner">
                                <p>
                                    Add a dependency to
                                    <a href="https://packagist.org/packages/phpdocumentor/phpdocumentor">phpdocumentor/phpdocumentor</a>
                                    to the <code>require-dev</code> section of your project's <code>composer.json</code>
                                    configuration file, and update your application.
                                </p>

                                <p>
                                    The following code is an example of a minimal <code>composer.json</code> file:
                                </p>
                                <pre><code class="language-javascript">{
    "require-dev": {
        "phpdocumentor/phpdocumentor": "2.*"
    }
}</code></pre>
                                <p>
                                    Once the installation is complete there will be a command <code>phpdoc.php</code> in
                                    the binary folder of your application (<code>/vendor/bin</code> by default).
                                </p>
                                <p class="alert alert-info">
                                    <strong>Hint</strong>: phpDocumentor consumes a fair amount of dependencies, if this is inconvenient
                                    then we suggest you choose one of the other installation options.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-group">
                        <div class="accordion-heading">
                            <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#installation" href="#install-phar">
                                <i class="icon-chevron-right"></i> As a PHAR
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <div id="install-phar" class="accordion-body collapse">
                            <div class="accordion-inner">
                                <p>
                                    <a href="http://phpdoc.org/phpDocumentor.phar">
                                        All you need to do is download the phar binary.
                                    </a>
                                </p>
                                <p>That's it. Really.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-group">
                        <div class="accordion-heading">
                            <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#installation" href="#install-manual">
                                <i class="icon-chevron-right"></i> Manually
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <div id="install-manual" class="accordion-body collapse">
                            <div class="accordion-inner">
                                <p>To do a manual installation, follow these steps</p>
                                <ol>
                                    <li>
                                        Locate the latest release on the
                                        <a href="https://github.com/phpDocumentor/phpDocumentor2/releases">releases page for phpDocumentor2 on GitHub</a>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>Download the attached tarball (not the source code!)</li>
                                    <li>Extract the downloaded tarball into your destination directory.</li>
                                </ol>
                                <p>
                                    After you have done the above can the executable be found at
                                    <code>bin/phpdoc.php</code> in the installation directory.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>
        </section>
    </section>

    </section>

                //Clear default text of emty text areas on focus
                function tFocus(element)
                {
                if (element.value == ' '){element.value='';}
                }
                //Clear default text of emty text areas on submit
                function tSubmit(form)
                {
                var defaultedElements = document.getElementsByTagName("textarea");
                for (var i=0; i != defaultedElements.length; i++){
                if (defaultedElements[i].value == ' '){
                defaultedElements[i].value='';}}
                }
                //Disable pressing 'enter' key to submit a form (otherwise pressing 'enter' causes a submission to start over)
                function disableEnterKey(e)
                {
                var key;

                if(window.event)
                key = window.event.keyCode;     //Internet Explorer
                else
                key = e.which;     //Firefox and Netscape

                if(key == 13)  //if "Enter" pressed, then disable!
                return false;
                else
                return true;
                }

<div>
<h2 class="ds-div-head page-header first-page-header">Apresenta&ccedil;&atilde;o</h2>
<div id="file_news_div_news" class="ds-static-div primary">
<p class="ds-paragraph">A Unesp - Universidade Estadual Paulista, no &acirc;mbito de seu Programa Mem&oacute;ria Social, d&aacute; in&iacute;cio ao processo de disponibiliza&ccedil;&atilde;o digital de acervos pertencentes ao seu sistema de bibliotecas e centros de documenta&ccedil;&atilde;o que re&uacute;ne documentos de naturezas diversas, tais como livros e peri&oacute;dicos, possibilitando &agrave; sociedade acessibilidade ao conhecimento.</p>
<p class="ds-paragraph">A parceria com a Biblioteca Nacional, o Arquivo P&uacute;blico do Estado de S&atilde;o Paulo e a Biblioteca M&aacute;rio de Andrade possibilitou, tamb&eacute;m, a reprodu&ccedil;&atilde;o de material pertencente a essas importantes institui&ccedil;&otilde;es p&uacute;blicas. Ao dar acesso irrestrito a esse rico material, a universidade cumpre com sua responsabilidade social, democratizando o acesso &agrave; informa&ccedil;&atilde;o e contribuindo com o ensino, a pesquisa e a difus&atilde;o do conhecimento.</p>
</div>

<h2 class="ds-div-head page-header">Communities in DSpace</h2>
<div id="aspect_artifactbrowser_CommunityBrowser_div_comunity-browser" class="ds-static-div primary">
<p class="ds-paragraph">Select a community to browse its collections.</p>
<div id="aspect_artifactbrowser_CommunityBrowser_referenceSet_community-browser" class="ds-static-div community-browser-wrapper">
<div class="ds-static-div row community-browser-row">
<div class="ds-static-div col-xs-10 col-sm-12 col-sm-offset-0 list-mode">
<a href="/handle/10/1" name="community-browser-link">Hemeroteca</a>
<p class="ds-paragraph hidden-xs">Re&uacute;ne publica&ccedil;&otilde;es peri&oacute;dicas, disponibilizadas integralmente, com possibilidade de pesquisa por t&iacute;tulo ou por palavras em seu conte&uacute;do completo.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="ds-static-div row community-browser-row odd-community-browser-row">
<div class="ds-static-div col-xs-10 col-sm-12 col-sm-offset-0 list-mode">
<a href="/handle/10/56" name="community-browser-link">Hist&oacute;ria de S&atilde;o Paulo</a>
<p class="ds-paragraph hidden-xs">Tem por objetivo dar acesso a documentos importantes para a reconstru&ccedil;&atilde;o da trajet&oacute;ria paulista, inaugurada com a cole&ccedil;&atilde;o Documentos Interessantes para a hist&oacute;ria e costumes de S&atilde;o Paulo, publicada pelo Arquivo do estado de S&atilde;o Paulo.</p>
</div>
</div>

<p class="ds-paragraph hidden-xs">Obras selecionadas dos acervos das bibliotecas da Unesp e de suas cole&ccedil;&otilde;es especiais.</p>
</div>
</div>

<a href="/handle/10/109" name="community-browser-link">Mapas - S&atilde;o Paulo</a>
</div>
</div>
<div class="ds-static-div row community-browser-row">
<div class="ds-static-div col-xs-10 col-sm-12 col-sm-offset-0 list-mode">
<a href="/handle/10/79" name="community-browser-link">M&uacute;sica</a>
<p class="ds-paragraph hidden-xs">Acervo de partituras do Maestro Furio Franceschini, importante por apresentar a m&uacute;sica sacra composta em S&atilde;o Paulo, no s&eacute;culo XX.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

			</tr>
		</table>
	</div>

Site Oficial do Governo do Estado de São Paulo (http://www.saopaulo.sp.gov.br)
Assessoria de Comunicação da Prodesp

<head>
	<title>Portal da Transparência do Estado de São Paulo</title>
	
	<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1" />
	<meta name="author" content="Prodesp" />
	<meta name="keywords" content="portal da transparencia estadual de sao paulo, portal da transparencia sao paulo" /> 
  
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=9"/>

    
	<script type="text/javascript" src="js/external.js"></script>
        
	<script type="text/javascript"> 
	// Menu Drop Down Acessível
	// Alexandre Junqueira
	// con...@alexandrejunqueira.com
	// http://www.alexandrejunqueira.com/projetos/menu-drop-down-acessivel/ 
	var dropdown_intervalId;
	var dropdown_ulId = (!dropdown_ulId) ? 'cxs-home' : dropdown_ulId;
	var dropdown_delay = (!dropdown_delay) ? 0 : dropdown_delay;
	 
	function dropdown_init()
	{
	 try
	 {
	  var as = document.getElementById(dropdown_ulId).getElementsByTagName('a');
	  
	  for (var a = 0; a < as.length; a++)
	  {
	   as[a].onfocus = function() { dropdown_expand(this) }
	   as[a].onmouseover = function() { dropdown_expand(this) }
	   as[a].onblur = function() { dropdown_colapse(dropdown_delay) } 
	   as[a].onmouseout = function() { dropdown_colapse(dropdown_delay) }
	  }
	  
	  dropdown_colapse(0);
	 
	 } catch(e){}
	}
	 
	function dropdown_expand(caller)
	{ 
	 try
	 { 
	  clearInterval(dropdown_intervalId);
	  
	  var uls = caller.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('ul');
	  
	  for (var ul = 0; ul < uls.length; ul++)
	   uls[ul].style.left = "-1000em";
	  
	  caller.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('ul')[0].style.left = "auto";
	  
	 } catch(e){} 
	}
	 
	function dropdown_colapse(milliseconds)
	{
	 try
	 {
	  clearInterval(dropdown_intervalId);
	  
	  dropdown_intervalId = setInterval(function()
	  {    
	   var uls = document.getElementById(dropdown_ulId).getElementsByTagName('ul');
	   
	   for (var ul = 0; ul < uls.length; ul++)
		uls[ul].style.left = "-1000em";
		
	   clearInterval(dropdown_intervalId);
	   
	  }, milliseconds, null);
	  
	 } catch(e){}
	}
	 
	window.onload = dropdown_init;
	</script>



	<!-- versao 1.0 -->
    
</head>

						<li><a href="https://portal.fazenda.sp.gov.br/acessoinformacao/Paginas/Beneficios-Fiscais-Reconhecidos.aspx" target="_blank">Benef&iacute;cios Fiscais  Reconhecidos</a></li>
		</ul>
 </li>
 
 <li class="cx-info btn">
 				
				<a href="https://portal.fazenda.sp.gov.br/acessoinformacao/Paginas/Web-Services.aspx" target="_blank" class="txt_info tooltip">Web Service
				<span class="ttipcontent">Permite consulta sobre receitas e despesas em formato de dados abertos. </span>	
				</a></li>
 
 <li class="cx-info btn">
 				<a href="http://www.governo.sp.gov.br/OSsobre.html" target="_blank" class="txt_info tooltip">Organiza&ccedil;&otilde;es Sociais
				<span class="ttipcontent">Qualifica&ccedil;&atilde;o dada &agrave;s entidades privadas sem finalidade lucrativa respons&aacute;veis pela gest&atilde;o de equipamentos p&uacute;blicos ou execu&ccedil;&atilde;o de atividades de interesse coletivo nas &aacute;reas de: (i) sa&uacute;de; (ii) cultura; (iii) esporte; (iv) direitos da pessoa com defici&ecirc;ncia; (v) direitos de crian&ccedil;as e adolescentes; (vi) meio ambiente; e (vii) investimentos, competitividade e desenvolvimento. </span>
				</a></li>		
				
 
<li class="cx-info btn">
 				<span style="text-align:right"> <a class="tooltip ico-tooltip" href="#"><span class="ttipcontent">Cadastro das entidades sem fins lucrativos que pretendem celebrar ou j&aacute; mant&eacute;m ajustes e/ou recebem benef&iacute;cios do Estado.</span></a></span>	
				<a href="#" class="txt_info2">Cadastro Estadual de Entidades</a>
 					<ul class="subitem-cx">
						<li><a href="http://www.cadastrodeentidades.sp.gov.br/" target="_blank">Cadastro Estadual de Entidades - CEE</a></li>
						<li><a href="http://www.corregedoria.sp.gov.br/conteudo/crce.html" target="_blank">Certificado de Regularidade Cadastral de Entidades - CRCE</a></li>
						<li><a href="http://www.cadastrodeentidades.sp.gov.br/consultapublica.aspx" target="_blank">Relat&oacute;rio de Entidades Certificadas</a></li>
						<li><a href="http://www.cadastrodeentidades.sp.gov.br/RelatorioDominioPublico.aspx" target="_blank">Lista das Entidades Cadastradas no CEE</a></li>
						<li><a href="empresas_proibidas.html">Empresas/Pessoas F&iacute;sicas proibidas de contratar com o Estado</a></li>
					</ul>
 
 </li>
 
 <li class="cx-info btn">
		<a href="adm_publica.html" class="txt_info tooltip">Administra&ccedil;&atilde;o P&uacute;blica
				<span class="ttipcontent">Informa&ccedil;&otilde;es sobre a organiza&ccedil;&atilde;o administrativa do Estado, dos respectivos dirigentes at&eacute; o 3&ordm; escal&atilde;o e rela&ccedil;&atilde;o dos im&oacute;veis pr&oacute;prios do Estado.</span>
				</a></li>
                
<li class="cx-info btn">
 				<a href="http://www.concursopublico.sp.gov.br/" target="_blank" class="txt_info tooltip">Concursos P&uacute;blicos
				<span class="ttipcontent">Site oficial dos Concursos Públicos do Estado de São Paulo.</span>
				</a></li>                
 
 
 <li class="cx-info btn">
 				<span style="text-align:right"> <a class="tooltip ico-tooltip" href="#"><span class="ttipcontent">Acesso a todas as informa&ccedil;&otilde;es referentes &agrave;s parcerias p&uacute;blico-privadas, inclusive dos projetos em andamento.</span></a></span>	
				<a href="http://www.governo.sp.gov.br/PED-PPPprojetos.html" target="_blank" class="txt_info2">Concessões - Parcerias Público-Privadas</a>

</ul>

    <h2 class="title">SH - Secretaria da Habita&ccedil;&atilde;o</h2>
        <div id="ca-container" class="ca-container">
		    <div class="ca-wrapper">
                <div class="ca-item ca-item-1">
				    <div class="ca-item-main">
					    <div class="ca-icon"></div>
					    <h3><a id="cplcontent_shmunicipios" href="http://app.habitacao.sp.gov.br/InfoHabMunicipio" target="_blank">Munic&iacute;pios</a><br /><a id="cplcontent_shprincipal" href="http://app.casapaulista.sp.gov.br/cpadministracao" target="_blank">Secretaria</a><a id="cplcontent_shext" href="http://app.casapaulista.sp.gov.br/cpext" target="_blank"><br />Agente Financeiro</a><br /><a id="cplcontent_hlagpromotor" class="dialog-construcao"><span style="cursor:pointer">Agente Promotor</span></a></h3>
					    <a href="#" class="ca-more">leia +</a>
				    </div>
				    <div class="ca-content-wrapper">
					    <div class="ca-content">
						    <h6>SIHAB - Sistema de Informa&ccedil;&otilde;es Habitacionais</h6>
						    <a href="#" class="ca-close">fechar</a>
						    <div class="ca-content-text">
							    <p>O&nbsp;<strong>Sistema de Informa&ccedil;&otilde;es Habitacionais &ndash; SIHAB</strong>&nbsp;&eacute; uma base de dados onde estar&atilde;o concentradas as informa&ccedil;&otilde;es habitacionais dos Munic&iacute;pios...</p>
						    </div>
						    <ul>
							    <li><a id="cplcontent_HyperLink1" href="casapaulista/sihab.aspx">Leia o texto completo</a></li>
						    </ul>
					    </div>
				    </div>
			    </div>
			    <div class="ca-item ca-item-2">
				    <div class="ca-item-main">
					    <div class="ca-icon"></div>
					    <h3>Grupo de An&aacute;lise e Aprova&ccedil;&atilde;o de Projetos Habitacionais</h3>
					    <a href="#" class="ca-more">leia +</a>
				    </div>
				    <div class="ca-content-wrapper">
					    <div class="ca-content">
						    <h6>Grupo de An&aacute;lise e Aprova&ccedil;&atilde;o de Projetos Habitacionais</h6>
						    <a href="#" class="ca-close">fechar</a>
						    <div class="ca-content-text">
							    <p>O <strong>GRAPROHAB - Grupo de An&aacute;lise e Aprova&ccedil;&atilde;o de Projetos Habitacionais do Estado de S&atilde;o Paulo</strong> foi reestruturado...</p>
						    </div>
						    <ul>
							    <li><a id="cplcontent_hlGraprohab" href="secretariahabitacao/graprohab.aspx">Leia o texto completo</a></li>
                                <!--<li><a id="cplcontent_hlSisGraprohab" href="secretariahabitacao/graprohab/sistema_graprohab.aspx">GRAPROHAB Digital</a></li>-->
						    </ul>
					    </div>
				    </div>
			    </div>

				    </div>

						    <h6>Cadastro de Beneficiados em Programas Habitacionais</h6>

			    <div class="ca-item ca-item-4">

				    </div>

						    <div class="ca-content-text">
							    <p>O Programa &ldquo;Cidade Legal&rdquo; foi criado em agosto de 2007 com o objetivo de implementar, agilizar e desburocratizar...</p>
						    </div>

				    </div>
			    </div>
                <div class="ca-item ca-item-5">
				    <div class="ca-item-main">
					    <div class="ca-icon"></div>
					    <h3>Conhe&ccedil;a melhor a Secretaria da Habita&ccedil;&atilde;o</h3>
					    <a href="#" class="ca-more">leia +</a>
				    </div>
				    <div class="ca-content-wrapper">
					    <div class="ca-content">
						    <h6>Informa&ccedil;&otilde;es sobre a Secretaria da Habita&ccedil;&atilde;o</h6>
						    <a href="#" class="ca-close">fechar</a>
						    <div class="ca-content-text">
							    <p>A Secretaria da Habita&ccedil;&atilde;o &eacute; respons&aacute;vel pela condu&ccedil;&atilde;o da pol&iacute;tica habitacional do Governo do Estado de S&atilde;o Paulo.</p>
						    </div>
						    <ul>

					    </div>
				    </div>
			    </div>
                <div class="ca-item ca-item-6">
				    <div class="ca-item-main">

						    </div>

            function show() {
                var menu = $(this);
                menu.children(".actions").slideDown();
            }

            function hide() {
                var menu = $(this);
                menu.children(".actions").slideUp();
            }

            $(".hover-menu").hoverIntent({
                sensitivity: 1, // number = sensitivity threshold (must be 1 or higher)
                interval: 50,   // number = milliseconds for onMouseOver polling interval
                over: show,     // function = onMouseOver callback (required)
                timeout: 300,   // number = milliseconds delay before onMouseOut
                out: hide       // function = onMouseOut callback (required)
            });

        });

    <div style="float: left; width: 280px;">
        <div class="txt_titulos" style="float: left; width: 260px; border-top: #034ea2 4px solid;
            border-bottom: #034ea2 1px solid;">
            Bem-vindo</div>
        <div align="justify" style="width: 240px; margin-left: 12px; height: 334px;" class="txt_space20">
            <br />
            <br />
            A Lei de Acesso à Informação, instituída pela <a href="http://www.planalto.gov.br/CCIVIL_03/_Ato2011-2014/2011/Lei/L12527.htm"
                target="_blank" class="Links">Lei Federal nº 12.527</a>, de 18 de novembro de
            2011, e o <a href="http://www.legislacao.sp.gov.br/legislacao/dg280202.nsf/5fb5269ed17b47ab83256cfb00501469/0d8cf8dcbd4ef45f83257a010046ef75?OpenDocument"
                target="_blank" class="Links">decreto estadual que a regulamenta, nº 58.052</a>,
            de 16 de maio de 2012 cria o Serviço de Informações ao Cidadão  SIC, no qual é
            possível solicitar documentos e dados relativos aos órgãos e entidades da Administração
            Pública Paulista.
            
        </div>
    </div>

                                                                <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-6">
                                    <h3 class="section-title">Ações do Governo</h3>

                                                                            <div class="row">

                                            
                                                <div class="col-md-6 featured-box">
                                                    <figure class="thumb-image">
                                                        <a class="wrap-image" href="http://www.saopaulo.sp.gov.br/acoes-governo/agricultura-e-abastecimento/"><img class="wp-image-thumb img-responsive image" src="http://www.saopaulo.sp.gov.br/wp-content/uploads/old/7217/31235-263x323.jpg" width="263" height="323" alt="Melhorias na merenda escolar, subsistência e geração de renda" /></a>                                                        <figcaption class="legend">

<div id="main">
	<h2 class="free_oss">THE #1 FREE, OPEN SOURCE BULLETIN BOARD SOFTWARE</h2>

	<p>phpBB is a free flat-forum bulletin board software solution that can be used to stay in touch with a group of people or can power your entire website.  With an <a href="/customise/db/extensions-36">extensive database of user-created extensions</a> and <a href="/customise/db/styles-2">styles database</a> containing hundreds of style and image packages to customise your board, you can create a very unique forum in minutes.</p>

	<p>No other bulletin board software offers a greater complement of features, while maintaining efficiency and ease of use.  Best of all, phpBB is completely free.  We welcome you to <a href="/demo/">test it</a> for yourself today.  If you have any questions please visit our <a href="/community/">Community Forum</a> where our staff and members of the community will be happy to assist you with anything from configuring the software to modifying the code for individual needs.  <a href="/about/">Learn more about phpBB.</a></p>

	<hr />

<!-- launch countdown timer. Can be removed after launch -->
<script type="text/javascript" src="/assets/js/jquery.countdown.min.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript">
	$(function() {
		var $timerBox = $('#countdown-timer');
		$timerBox.html('<span class="timer-big">00</span><span class="timer-small">time left</span>');
		var $timerBig = $timerBox.find('.timer-big');
		var $timerSmall = $timerBox.find('.timer-small');
		var number = '';
		var unit = '';

		var utc = new Date('Sat Jan 07 2017 17:00:00 GMT+0000 (UTC)').getTime();

		$timerBox.countdown(utc).on('update.countdown', function(event) {
			if (event.offset.totalDays > 0) {
				number = event.strftime('%D');
				unit = 'days left';
			} else if (event.offset.hours > 0) {
				number = event.strftime('%H');
				unit = 'hours left';
			} else if (event.offset.minutes > 0) {
				number = event.strftime('%M');
				unit = 'minutes';
			} else if (event.offset.seconds > 0) {
				number = event.strftime('%S');
				unit = 'seconds';
			}
			$timerBig.html('3.2');
			$timerSmall.html('is coming!');
		}).on('finish.countdown', function() {
			$timerBig.html('3.2');
			$timerSmall.html('is here!');
		});

		$timerBox.show();
	});
</script>

  <div class="mobile-title"><h3><a href="blog/network-outage-2016-12-17/">Network Outage 2016-12-17 Post-mortem</a></h3></div>
<div id="features">
    <div class='region region-features'>
      <div class="mobile-content">
        <img class='summary-image' alt="" src="https://osuosl.org/images/ "></img>
      </div>

        <div id="block-views-feature-story-block" class="block block-views">
            <div class="content">
                <div class="view view-feature-story view-id-feature_story view-display-id-block">
                    <div class='view-content front-page-story'>
                                <div class='fs-row'>
                                    <a href="blog/summer-2016-internship/">
                                        <img class='summary-image' alt="" src="https://osuosl.org/images/Interns2016-1.jpg "></img>
                                    </a>
                                    <div class="views-field-field-caption">
                                        <h3 class="fs-title">
                                            <a href="blog/summer-2016-internship/">
                                                OSL Summer 2016 Internship
                                            </a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <p class="fs-caption">
                                        <p>In a new program, the Oregon State University Open Source Lab (OSL) partnered
with Intel to give community college students an opportunity to get hands-on
experience with open-source projects. This summer, four students interned for 10
weeks at the OSL, working on a variety of projects, including web development
and systems engineering, to advance their skills and knowledge with ...</p>
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class='fs-row'>
                                    <a href="blog/pycon-2016/">
                                        <img class='summary-image' alt="" src="https://osuosl.org/images/PyCon16-logo.png "></img>
                                    </a>
                                    <div class="views-field-field-caption">
                                        <h3 class="fs-title">
                                            <a href="blog/pycon-2016/">
                                                The OSL at PyCon
                                            </a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <p class="fs-caption">
                                        <p>The month of June opened with the annual <a class="reference external" href="https://us.pycon.org/2016/">PyCon</a> event at the Oregon Convention
Center in Portland, the largest annual gathering for the <a class="reference external" href="https://www.python.org">Python</a> community.
This year, the OSL had the opportunity to send one of its own. </p>
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class='fs-row'>
                                    <a href="blog/graduation-2016/">
                                        <img class='summary-image' alt="" src="https://osuosl.org/images/Graduation2016PostPicture.png "></img>
                                    </a>
                                    <div class="views-field-field-caption">
                                        <h3 class="fs-title">
                                            <a href="blog/graduation-2016/">
                                                Congratulations 2016 Graduates!
                                            </a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <p class="fs-caption">
                                        <p>As exciting as the end of the school year is for everyone, and with it the
promise of sun, no classes, shorts, extended vacations, and no classes, it also
brings an inevitable goodbye to those leaving to enter the real world.</p>
<p>I'm talking about our graduating seniors. Those who have earned their stripes
and are ready to move on. The superstars stepping up to take the stage. The
brave ...</p>
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class='fs-row'>
                                    <a href="blog/rtems/">
                                        <img class='summary-image' alt="" src="https://osuosl.org/images/windows-on-building.jpg "></img>
                                    </a>
                                    <div class="views-field-field-caption">
                                        <h3 class="fs-title">
                                            <a href="blog/rtems/">
                                                RTEMS
                                            </a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <p class="fs-caption">
                                        <p>Within the last several years, the OSL has provided a home for the Real-Time
Executive for Multiprocessor System, or RTEMS. RTEMS is an open Real-Time
Operating System (RTOS) that supports both open application programming
interfaces (API) and interfacing standards such as Berkeley sockets. Basically,
RTEMS supports the embedded systems in programs, or the combinations of
software and ...</p>
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class='fs-row'>
                                    <a href="blog/cass-allseen-alliance/">
                                        <img class='summary-image' alt="" src="https://osuosl.org/images/AllSeen-Alliance-Picture.png "></img>
                                    </a>
                                    <div class="views-field-field-caption">
                                        <h3 class="fs-title">
                                            <a href="blog/cass-allseen-alliance/">
                                                CASS and the AllSeen Alliance
                                            </a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <p class="fs-caption">
                                        <p>Oregon State University has joined the worlds technology leaders  including
LG, Microsoft, and Qualcomm  to advance the collaborative development of the
Internet of Things (IoT).</p>
<p>IoT is a network of devices that exchange information  anything from
smaller devices like watches to full-scale smart cities. IoT devices are
almost too numerous to count, including light bulbs, air ...</p>
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                    </div>

                    <a id='prev' class="side-controls previous slick-prev">
                        <span class='icon-chevron-left'>&#8249;</span>
                    </a>
                    <a id='next' class="side-controls next slick-next">
                        <span class='icon-chevron-left'>&#8250;</span>

                </div>
                <!-- <div class="mobile-content">
                  <img class='summary-image' alt="" src="https://osuosl.org/images/ "></img>
                </div> -->
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


 
 
 
 
 
 
            <p>The Open Source Lab is a nonprofit organization working for the advancement of
open source technologies.</p>
<p>The lab, in partnership with the School of Electrical Engineering and Computer
Science at Oregon State University, provides hosting for more than 160 projects,
including those of worldwide leaders like the Apache Software Foundation, the
Linux Foundation and Drupal. Together, the OSLs hosted sites deliver nearly 430
terabytes of information to people around the world every month. The most active
organization of its kind, the OSL offers world-class hosting services,
professional software development and on-the-ground training for promising
students interested in open source management and programming.</p>
<!-- .. image:: /images/edray.jpg
:scale: 100%
:align: center
:alt: OSU President Ed Ray -->
<p>By enabling innovative projects and distributing software to millions of users
globally, the lab is working to accelerate the growth of high-impact open source
software projects and promote an open source culture of accessibility and
increased productivity around the world. The lab partners with industry leaders
and policy makers to bring open source technologies to new sectors, including
education, health and government.</p>
<p>Under the school of EECS, the OSL and the Oregon State Business Solutions Group
have joined together to create the Center for Applied Systems and Software
(CASS). CASS provides clients with services for every stage of a project:
designing, developing, testing and hosting. This partnership allows each group
to maintain its unique brand while combining their expertise and giving them the
ability and resources to take on bigger and better projects.</p>
<p>To learn more about obtaining services from the lab and explore our active
projects, please visit our Hosting and Development pages. A list of our hosted
projects can be found on our Hosted Communities page. To get updates on the Open
Source Lab, read our Blog page. If you are interested in contributing to the
success of our projects or sponsoring our students' progress, please visit our
Donate page.</p>

<div id="block-livefeedsnews-2" data-block-plugin-id="live_feeds_news">
  
      <h2>News</h2>
    
      <div class="live-feeds-block">
    
        
            
                    <div class="news-item">
                <img class="imagefield imagefield-field_thumbnail" width="75" height="75" alt="OSU News Release" src="http://oregonstate.edu/ua/ncs/sites/default/files/releases/thumbs/arctic_lter_small.jpg?1490205723" />
                <h3 class="title">
                    <a href="http://oregonstate.edu/ua/ncs/archives/2017/mar/oregon-state-part-new-nsf-research-program-arctic">Oregon State part of new NSF research program in the Arctic</a>
                </h3>
                <div class="date">
                    Mar 22, 2017
                </div>
                <div class="news-body">
                    Oregon State University is part of s new Long-Term Ecological Research (LTER) project in the Arctic that will explore how relationships between the land and water affect coastal ecosystems.
                </div>
            </div>
                    <div class="news-item">
                <img class="imagefield imagefield-field_thumbnail" width="75" height="75" alt="OSU News Release" src="http://oregonstate.edu/ua/ncs/sites/default/files/releases/thumbs/square_354.jpg?1489682874" />
                <h3 class="title">
                    <a href="http://oregonstate.edu/ua/ncs/archives/2017/mar/dietary-anti-cancer-compound-may-work-influence-cellular-genetics">Dietary anti-cancer compound may work by influence on cellular genetics</a>
                </h3>
                <div class="date">
                    Mar 16, 2017
                </div>
                <div class="news-body">
                    Researchers have found that sulforaphane, a dietary compound from broccoli thats helps prevent prostate cancer, may work through its influence on long, non-coding RNAs.
                </div>
            </div>
                    <div class="news-item">
                <img class="imagefield imagefield-field_thumbnail" width="75" height="75" alt="OSU News Release" src="http://oregonstate.edu/ua/ncs/sites/default/files/releases/thumbs/juvenile_chinook_small.jpg?1489523153" />
                <h3 class="title">
                    <a href="http://oregonstate.edu/ua/ncs/archives/2017/mar/anomalous-ocean-conditions-2015-may-bode-poorly-juvenile-chinook-salmon-survival">Anomalous ocean conditions in 2015 may bode poorly for juvenile Chinook salmon survival</a>
                </h3>
                <div class="date">
                    Mar 14, 2017
                </div>
                <div class="news-body">
                    Fisheries managers have been predicting a slightly below-average run of spring Chinook salmon on the Columbia River this year but a newly published suggests that it may be worse.
                </div>
            </div>
            </div>

  </div>

    <div id="block-homepage-content" data-block-plugin-id="system_main_block">
  
    
      <article role="article" about="/node/1">

  
    

  
  <div>
    
      <div>
              <div>        
<div class="paragraph paragraph--type--paragraph-2-column paragraph--view-mode--default row">
    <div class="col-md-6 " >
        
            <div><h3>A global leader, a statewide partner</h3>

<p>With a record $336 million in external research funding in 2016, Oregon State researchers are leaders and innovators in natural resources, technology, agriculture, public health and other areas. The economic impact of Oregon States research enterprise: $762 million statewide and globally, according to ECONorthwest. Oregons leading public research university partners with communities and businesses across the state, the nation and the world to solve our most challenging problems.</p>

<ul><li><a href="http://research.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Research Office');">Research Office</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://terra.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Terra');">Terra</a>  Oregon States research magazine</li>
</ul></div>
      
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 light_text" style=background-image:url(/sites/default/files/2017-02/AunaGodinez-min.jpg)>
        
            <div><div style="position:absolute;bottom:10px;left:10px;right:10px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.9);color:#373a3c;padding:10px;">
<h4>Learning beyond the classroom</h4>

<p><a style="color:#c34500;" href="http://poweredbyorange.com/2016/02/26/natural-beauty/">Auna Godinez</a> has explored her interest in renewable materials through <a style="color:#c34500;" href="http://undergraduate.oregonstate.edu/research/">undergraduate research</a>, <a style="color:#c34500;" href="http://international.oregonstate.edu/osugo/study-abroad-programs">study abroad</a> and field work in the forests of Peru.</p>


<p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="http://oregonstate.edu/admissions/main/apply-choose-application" style="text-decoration:none;">Apply Now</a></p>
</div>
</div>
      
    </div>
</div>
</div>
              <div>    
<div class="left-text paragraph paragraph--type--paragraph-1-column paragraph--view-mode--default row">
    <div class="col-md-12" style=background-image:url(/sites/default/files/paragraphs/courthouse-compressor_0.jpg)>
        
            <div><div style="background:rgba(0,0,0,.7);padding:20px;">
<h3>Oregons statewide university begins in Corvallis</h3>

<p>Oregon State Universitys hometown is consistently ranked among the best college towns in the nation  as well as one of the smartest, safest and most sustainable. <a href="http://oregonstate.edu/admissions/static/corvallis/#.Va2SRcZVhkI">Learn all the reasons</a> why Corvallis is a great place to live and learn.</p>

<p>And Corvallis is just a starting point. Oregon State brings leadership, innovation and excellence to every corner of Oregon. That includes education, pharmacy, veterinary medicine and professional MBA programs in Portland, world-class marine science programs in Newport and <a href="http://osucascades.edu/">OSU-Cascades</a>, its four-year campus in Bend.</p>

<ul><li><a href="http://portland.oregonstate.edu/">PORTLAND</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://osucascades.edu/">BEND</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://hmsc.oregonstate.edu/">NEWPORT</a></li>
</ul></div>
</div>
      
    </div>
</div>
</div>
              <div>        
<div class="left-text black_bg_right bg_padding light_text paragraph paragraph--type--paragraph-2-column paragraph--view-mode--default row">
    <div class="col-md-6 light_text" style=background-image:url(/sites/default/files/2016-08/marine-compressor-compressor.jpg)>
        
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 " >
        
            <div><h3>Saving the oceans, saving the world</h3>

<p>The <a href="http://marinestudies.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Marine Studies');">Marine Studies Initiative</a> is a university-wide commitment and a new model for teaching, research and outreach to address emerging issues and challenges facing the worlds oceans. It builds on Oregon States deep history of nationally ranked programs, world-leading research and premier facilities to help sustain healthy oceans and ensure wellness, environmental health and economic prosperity for future generations.</p>

<p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://youtu.be/6DD6lID4R8A" style="text-decoration:none;">Watch Video</a></p>
</div>
      
    </div>
</div>
</div>
              <div>
<div class="force-dark left-text paragraph paragraph--type--paragraph-2-column paragraph--view-mode--default row">
    <div class="col-md-6 " >
        
            <div><h3>A 21st century land grant for Oregon, the nation and the world</h3>

<p>Designated the states land grant institution in 1868, Oregon State University continues to fulfill its mission of accessible education, problem-solving research and outreach that serves communities statewide. Oregon is our natural laboratory, and with a presence in all 36 counties  from coast to valley, mountains to high desert, cities to farms and ranches  our impact reaches across Oregon and beyond.</p>
</div>
      
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 " >
        
            <div><ul><li><a href="http://extension.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Extension');">Extension Service</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://pace.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'PACE');">Professional and Continuing Education</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://summer.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Summer Session');">Summer Session</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://ecampus.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Ecampus');">Ecampus</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://oregonprogress.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Ag Progress');">Oregon's Agricultural Progress</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://fic.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Food Innovation Center');">Food Innovation Center</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://osuseafoodlab.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Seafood Lab');">Seafood Research and Extension Center</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://hmsc.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Hatfield');">Hatfield Marine Science Center</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://seagrant.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Sea Grant');">Sea Grant</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://spacegrant.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Space Grant');">Space Grant</a></li>
	<li><a href="http://sungrant.oregonstate.edu/" onclick="ga('send', 'event', 'viewbook', 'Sun Grant');">Sun Grant</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
    </div>
</div>
</div>
          </div>
  
  </div>

<h1>SciPy.org<a class="headerlink" href="#scipy-org" title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h1>

</table><p>SciPy (pronounced Sigh Pie) is a Python-based ecosystem
of open-source software for mathematics, science, and engineering. In
particular, these are some of the core packages:</p>
<div>
<ul class="thumbnails packageicons">

<li class="span4">
<div class="thumbnail">
<div class="pull-left img">
  <a href="http://numpy.org">
  <img alt="numpy" src="_static/images/numpylogo_med.png" width="64">
  </a>
</div>
<div class="img-label">
  <h4 class="media-heading"><a href="http://numpy.org">NumPy</a></h4>
  Base N-dimensional array package
</div>
</div>
</li>

<li class="span4">
<div class="thumbnail">
<div class="pull-left img">
  <a href="scipylib/index.html">
  <img alt="scipy" src="_static/images/scipy_med.png" width="64">
  </a>
</div>
<div class="img-label">
  <h4 class="media-heading"><a href="scipylib/index.html">SciPy library</a></h4>
  Fundamental library for scientific computing
</div>
</div>
</li>

<li class="span4">
<div class="thumbnail">
<div class="pull-left img">
  <a href="http://matplotlib.org/">
  <img alt="matplotlib" src="_static/images/matplotlib_med.png" width="64">
  </a>
</div>
<div class="img-label">
  <h4 class="media-heading"><a href="http://matplotlib.org/">Matplotlib</a></h4>
  Comprehensive 2D Plotting
</div>
</div>
</li>

<li class="span4">
<div class="thumbnail">
<div class="pull-left img">
  <a href="http://ipython.org">
  <img alt="ipython" src="_static/images/ipython.png" width="64">
  </a>
</div>
<div class="img-label">
  <h4 class="media-heading"><a href="http://ipython.org">IPython</a></h4>
  Enhanced Interactive Console
</div>
</div>
</li>

<li class="span4">
<div class="thumbnail">
<div class="pull-left img">
  <a href="http://sympy.org/">
  <img alt="sympy" src="_static/images/sympy_logo.png" width="64">
  </a>
</div>
<div class="img-label">
  <h4 class="media-heading"><a href="http://sympy.org/">Sympy</a></h4>
  Symbolic mathematics
</div>
</div>
</li>

<li class="span4">
<div class="thumbnail">
<div class="pull-left img">
  <a href="http://pandas.pydata.org/">
  <img alt="pandas badge" src="_static/images/pandas_badge2.jpg" width="64">
  </a>
</div>
<div class="img-label">
  <h4 class="media-heading"><a href="http://pandas.pydata.org/">pandas</a></h4>
  Data structures &amp; analysis
</div>
</div>
</li>

</ul>

<h2>News<a class="headerlink" href="#news" title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h2>

<dd>See <a class="reference internal" href="scipylib/download.html"><span class="doc">Obtaining NumPy &amp; SciPy libraries</span></a>.</dd>

<dd>See <a class="reference internal" href="scipylib/download.html"><span class="doc">Obtaining NumPy &amp; SciPy libraries</span></a>.</dd>

<dd>See <a class="reference internal" href="scipylib/download.html"><span class="doc">Obtaining NumPy &amp; SciPy libraries</span></a>.</dd>
